Anastomotic fistula is a serious complication which could last for several days or months. Although it is an observer-reported outcome, it would be based on the objective evidence such as drainage, laboratory examination, imageological examination, endoscopy, or surgery. In addition, it's generally not a one-time complication, the probability of misdiagnosis is relatively low.
